Package tile

package tile
The tile package provides classes for handling tiles in the game environment. It includes classes for individual tiles and a manager for efficiently managing tile-related operations.

The main classes in this package are:

  • Tile - Represents an individual tile in the game environment.
  • TileManager - Manages the creation, storage, and retrieval of tiles in the game.

Tile is a class specifically designed to represent an individual tile in the game. It encapsulates information about the tile's properties, such as its texture, terrain type, or interactive elements.

TileManager is a class that serves as a central component for managing tiles within the game. It includes methods for creating, storing, and retrieving tiles efficiently, facilitating the integration of tiles into the game environment.

The classes in this package play a crucial role in defining and managing the visual and interactive aspects of the game's tile-based environment.
